local gt = this.getroottable();

gt.Const.Strings.FT <- {
	SkillList = "[img]gfx/ui/events/event_15.png[/img]{1. Accidental Attack : Attack the target with melee weapon. Hit chance is reversed so the attack must miss to deal damage. (Melee Skill, Requirements: Melee Weapon) \n\n2. Acid Grenade : Throws an acid grenade at the target area, corroding armor and helmet. (Requirements: Crown) \n\n3. Backstab : Move behind the target and attack head and helmet. This skill always hits the head. Deals more damage to helm. (Melee Skill, Requirements: Dagger) \n\n4. Bear Trap : Place a bear trap on an empty tile. \n\n5. Berserker Charge : Charges to the target tile, attacking enemies around the landing tile. Damaged enemies are staggered. (Melee Skill) \n\n6. Black Magic Grenade : Throws a magic grenade that has a random negative effect on the target area. (Requirements: Crown) \n\n7. Blessing : Gives various beneficial effects to the target. \n\n8. Bloodletting Therapy : Heal yourself or an ally with bloodletting Therapy. \n\n9. Blood Lust : Increases combat power with blood lust. Can be used on self or allies. When casting a skill, the caster loses HP. \n\n10. Bribe : Bribe the target enemy. The target who received the bribe has a chance to give up the battle or defect. (Requirements: Crown) \n\n11. Cannon Barrage : After 2 turns, bombard the selected area. (Requirements: Crown) \n\n12-1. Brute Toss (Set Target) : Select a target to throw. \n12-2. Brute Toss (Toss) : Throws the selected target onto a designated empty tile to inflict damage. \n\n13. Battle Command : Command all allies to use Shield Wall, Spear Wall, and Riposte \n\n14. Concentration : Use all AP this turn. Gain beneficial buffs until the next turn. \n\n15. Perfect Aimed Throw : Deals powerful damage to an enemy located 3 tiles away. (Ranged Skill, Requirements: Javelin / Throwing Axe / Throwing Spear / Staff Sling / Spiked Bolas) \n\n16. Battle Cure : Removes various negative effects. (Requirements: Crown) \n\n17. Demonize : Gains great power through evil sorcery. But with great power comes great responsibility. \n\n18. Devastating Blow : Use a powerful strike with a melee weapon. It puts a lot of strain on the weapon. (Requirements: Melee Weapon) \n\n19. Drain Blood : Cast on a bleeding target to deal damage and restore the caster\'s fatigue. This effect is enhanced by stacks of bleeding on the target. \n\n20. Earthquake : Shakes the ground with magic, inflicting negative effects on targets in the area. Has no effect on caster himself. This skill is available 2 turns after the start of the battle. \n\n21. Electric Shock : Deal electrical damage to the target and stun. \n\n22. Feast : Feast on a corpse to regain health and reduce fatigue. \n\n23. Fire Ball : Casts a powerful fireball spell that explodes at the target location. Can hit many targets. (Ranged Skill) \n\n24. Hellfire Grenade : Throws a grenade that emits malicious magical flames, burning 7 tiles. (Requirements: Crown) \n\n25. Flame Wave : Burns and dazes multiple targets in a straight line. (Requirements: Crown) \n\n26. Fling Back : Throws the target behind the caster, dealing damage. (Melee Skill) \n\n27. Force of Nature : Roots and damages the target with poisonous vines. \n\n28. Wicked Frenzy : Steals the power of your allies to strengthen yourself. This effect lasts until the end of the battle. \n\n29. Frost Blast : Casts a powerful cold spell. The area affected by the skill turns into a snow tile, and units located at that point become cold. (Ranged Skill) \n\n30. Gale Force : A strong wind knocks the target back and deals damage. (Ranged Skill) \n\n31. Great Awakening : 51% chance for the caster to gain the following effects : Deal ranged skill damage to nearby enemies. Skill AP cost reduced by half for 1 turn. \n\n32. Headbutt : Deals damage to a single target. Always hit the head. (Melee Skill) \n\n33. Magical Healing : Restores a friendly target\'s health, armor and helmet. \n\n34. Hide : Hide and avoid enemy attacks until the next turn. Enemies do not react to movement while this effect lasts. (Ignore ZOC) \n\n35. Holy spear : Throws a holy spear filled with divine magic power at the enemy. Damage is increased if there are many friendly characters with this skill near the caster. (Ranged Skill) \n\n36. Judo throw : Throws the target behind the caster, dealing damage. Always 65% chance to hit. \n\n37. Kick : Attacks the enemy with a kick. Duelist perks apply. Can hit the head. (Melee Skill) \n\n38. Line Breaker : Knock the target 1 tile back, dealing damage. The caster moves to the location where the target was originally. (Melee Skill) \n\n39. Magical Lute Song : Sing a magical lute song to relieve the fatigue of allies. (Requirements: Lute) \n\n40. Thunderstorm : Inflicts ranged damage to random enemies within 2 tiles around you for 10 times. The caster cannot act for 2 turns. (Ranged Skill) \n\n41. Forced March : When not in melee combat, move 1 tile without using AP. \n\n42. Mark : Exposes the target\'s weaknesses and reduces melee and ranged defense. \n\n43. Miracle : Heal and lower fatigue nearby allies. No effect on self. \n\n44. Stealing : Steals crowns from target. Can only be used against humans and goblins. \n\n45. Multi Shot : Shoots arrows at up to 3 targets. (Ranged Skill, Requirements: Bow or Crossbow) \n\n46. Penetrating Shot : Penetrates the target with a powerful shot. Attacks up to 2 additional targets in a line behind the target. (Ranged Skill, Requirements: Bow or Crossbow) \n\n47. Pincer Thrust : Attack the target along with any allies with spears within 2 tile of the target. (Melee Skill, Requirements: Spear)  \n\n48. Telekinetic Explosion : Inflicts 25 fatigue to targets in the target area and pushes them out of the center.  \n\n49. Abyssal Grab : Pulls a distant enemy target towards you and binds it with tentacles. \n\n50. Purifying Flame : Cast a spell that exterminate undead in a wide area in front. Only affects enemy undead targets. \n\n51. Extreme Weather : Causes abnormal weather, reduces the melee skills, ranged skills, melee defense, and ranged defense of all enemies on the battlefield (Requirements: Crown) \n\n52. Courage Boost : Increases the target\'s morale to the maximum and decreases fatigue by 30. Can be used on allies. \n\n53. Boulder Throw : Throws a huge boulder at an enemy, dealing damage. Ranged damage type. Duelist perks apply. Can hit the head. (Ranged Skill) \n\n54. Throw Dirt : Throws dirt at the target, reducing attack power and initiative. \n\n55. Banshee Scream : Inflicts damage and negative effects on targets in a wide area in front. \n\n56. Shield Guard : Spend all AP this turn to reduce damage received by caster and target by 99% until the next turn. Caster lose 40% of the shield\'s durability. \n\n57. Shadow Walk : Ignore zone of control and teleports to the target tile. \n\n58. Shield Bash : Attack the target with a shield. Always 65% chance to hit. \n\n59. Shockwave : Create a shockwave with weapon to attack targets in a straight line. Can hit up to 5 targets in a straight line. (Melee Skillm, Requirements:Melee Weapon) \n\n60. Cursed Words : Reduces the morale of a single target. \n\n61. Serpent Bind : Binds the caster and target to two giant serpents. If either the caster or the target becomes unbound, so will the other. \n\n62. Double Edge : Attack the target (25% chance), or attack self (25% chance), or both (50% chance). (Requirements: Melee Weapon) \n\n63. Storm Fury : Only attacks enemies within 1 tile. This skill always deals max damage. (Melee Skill, Requirements: Melee Weapon) \n\n64. Fury Strike : Uses 100 fury points to strike the target 3 times. (Melee Skill, Requirements: Unarmed / Cestus) \n\n65. Summon Fiend : Summons a powerful monster for a limited time. \n\n66-1. Raise Dead : Resurrects a corpse as a skeleton minion. \n66-2 Unholy Bless : Make one of your skeleton minion permanently stronger with unholy magic. \n\n67. Summon Spirit Wolf : Summon Spirit Wolf and send him charging into the enemy. \n\n68. Forced Swap : Switch positions with the enemy. \n\n69. Grappling : 71% chance to inflict 25 fatigue and disarm the target. \n\n70. Tai Chi Weapon Form : Gain Riposte and Spearwall effects. Affected by Sword and Spear mastery. (Requirements: Melee Weapon) \n\n71. Silent Takedown : Sleep the enemy and tie up with a net to prevent movement. \n\n72. Unleash the Rage : Releases inner rage, greatly increasing combat abilities. \n\n73. War Crime : Inflict a horrific, unforgivable, inhumane act on a target with very low health. The target dies instantly. Can be used on both allies and enemies. \n\n74. Warcry : Let out a terrifying roar that negatively affects nearby enemies. \n\n75. Flood Bomb : Fills the 7 tiles containing the spot with a large amount of water, dealing damage and turning the terrain into a swamp. (Requirements: Crown) \n\n76. Whirlwind Attack : Only attacks enemies within 2 tile. (Melee Skill, Requirements: One-Handed Melee Weapon) \n\n77-1. Riding a Giant Wolf : Ride a giant wolf and defeat your enemies. \n77-2. Bite : The wolf bites the enemy \n\n78. Point Blank Shot : Attacks enemies with extremely powerful close-range fire. The powerful recoil can knock back targets and yourself.(Ranged Skill, Requirements: Handgonne / Hextech Rifle) \n\n79. Agile Killer (passive) : If you are faster than the target when attacking, you gain +9 melee and ranged skills. If you are faster than the attacker when attacked, you gain +9 melee and ranged defense. \n\n80. Transcendence (passive) : +2 All stats \n\n81. Banner Lord (passive) : When you use the Battle Standard (banner item), you gain +20 Damage, +7 Melee Skill, +7 Melee Defense, +7 Ranged Defense \n\n82. Battle Trance (passive) : You become stronger after using a lot of fatigue. \n\n83. Vengeance (passive) : Once per turn, when this character successfully attacks or dodges, deals 5 damage. (This damage cannot kill the target) \n\n84. Mana Mastery (passive) : When both hands are empty, the damage of a specific skill is enhanced. The higher your current Resolve, the greater the effect. \n\n85. Challenger (passive) : When you kill a human enemy with 450 or more experience, you and all allies recover 35 fatigue and gain 350 crowns. Works once per battle \n\n86. Adaptive Counter (passive) : Gain a bonus to Max Fatigue, Melee Skill, and Ranged Skill in proportion to Ranged Defense. \n\n87. Desolator (passive) : Increase AOE Damage with each following perk : #Crippling Strikes, #Executioner, #Fearsome \n\n88. Drunken Master (passive) : Increased combat skills when drunk. \n\n89. Goblin Weaponology (passive) : When using the Goblin named weapon: 50% chance to gain +100% Armor Penetration and +5 Melee Defense at the start of the turn (lasts 1 turn) \n\n90. Harden Skin (passive) : Beneficial effects can be achieved by not wearing armor, helmet. \n\n91. Head Collector (passive) : +15% Chance to hit head. When attacking, hitting the head restores 10 fatigue. \n\n92. Poor Man\'s Weapon (passive) : Gain beneficial effects when using a weak weapon. \n\n93. Kensei (passive) : Enhances the basic attack skill when using a sword. \n\n94. Last Stand (passive) : +100% damage increase when current morale status is Wavering or Breaking \n\n95. Lifestealer (passive) : When attacking, 30% damage lifesteal on hit \n\n96. Masochism (passive) : This character enjoys its own pain and becomes stronger as they take more damage. \n\n97. Oddball (passive) : Additional damage effects are applied to unpopular pucks. \n\n98. Orc Weaponology (passive) : When using an Orc weapon or shield: +7 Fatigue Recovery per turn \n\n99. Outsider (passive) : With no ally within 2 tiles of distance, gain a +9 bonus to Melee Skill, Ranged Skill, Melee Defense, Ranged Defense, and Resolve. \n\n100. Warm-up (passive) : +5 All Stats. But unable to act for 1 turns at the start of battle. \n\n101.  Prudence (passive) :  +12 Melee Defense, When Fleeing state: 50% chance become Breaking state at start of turn, Additional Action Point per tile moved \n\n102. Rapid Reflexes (passive) : +20 initiative. -20% reduced damage taken. \n\n103. Self Care (passive) : At the end of battle: Fully recover Armor, Helm, HP \n\n104. Sharpshooter (passive) : Grants bonus damage per tile of distance to the target when using a Bow or Crossbow skill. \n\n105. Skull Surgery (passive) : When using Flail or Mace: +12 Melee skill \n\n106. Steel Thorn (passive) : +10 Melee Skill and Defense when the you have the Spear Wall or Riposte buff \n\n107. Veteran (passive) : Melee and Ranged skills increase proportionally to the number of working days. \n\n108. Propaganda : Control the Reputation and Renown of your mercenary group with this skill. \n\n109. Honest Attacker (passive) : Damage increased by +30%. Head attack probability is reduced to 0%. \n\n110. Shield of Faith (passive) : When equipped with a Shield : +25 Max Fatigue +10 Bravery (This effect is doubled when it is a named or legendary shield) \n\n111. Dragon Tooth Kick : Jumps towards a target 2 tiles away and strikes with a powerful flying kick. When hit, the target is knocked back. \n\n112. Wrath of Davkul : Deals damage to all enemies after 3 turns. (Requirements: Crown) \n\n113. Armageddon : Damages everyone. (Requirements: Crown) \n\n114. Swarm of Insects : Summons a swarm of insects to weaken the target. \n\n115. Uproot : Massive roots emerge from the ground, damaging two targets in a straight line and inflicting the Staggered status. \n\n116. Battle Domination : Enemies with specific states on the battlefield have their damage dealt reduced and damage received increased. \n\n117. Tactical Bluff (passive) : Takes reduced damage and gains bonus resolve for the first few turns. \n\n118. Poking : A quick attack, with a random hit chance penalty applied in each battle. (Melee skill, Requirements: Dagger / One-Handed Sword / One-Handed Spear)  \n\n119. Spirit Swipe : Inflicts bleeding on enemies in the selected area, ignoring bleed immunity. \n\n120. Combat Rhythm : Gain bonus damage every multiple of 3 turns. \n\nLinked Skill Group : (#17, 73), (#25, 23), (#36, 26), (#36, 38), (#85, 107), (#91, 105), (#95, 19), (#111, 37), (#82, 84, 108) (When you collect all the skills with specific numbers that are linked together, a special effect will be triggered on the skill marked with #)}"
	PortalGateName = "Portal Gate"
	PortalGateText = "Mystic energies swirl within this portal, allowing instant travel to other towns."
	NoUse = "[color=" + this.Const.UI.Color.NegativeValue + "]Currently Unavailable[/color]"
